						               													<description>The Backwards Game is a party game played in teams in which all of the questions and challenges are incredibly easy...if you do them forwards. However, in this game, EVERYTHING happens in reverse.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of a game, each team decides on a secret five letter word, e.g., B-R-E-A-D, which they write backwards on their &amp;quot;backwards board&amp;quot; and cover up with five mystery cards. Each team has thirty seconds to whizz through as many backwards clues as possible across five types of clue card. After thirty seconds, the team scores how many correct answers they got by ticking them off inside the circles on the backwards board. When a team ticks off three of the circles, they can try to guess a letter on the rival team's backwards board. If the letter they guess is in the other team's word, that team must reveal it by removing the mystery card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first team to correctly guess the rival's team secret word and say it forwards wins. However, if they make an incorrect guess, the opposing team can remove any mystery card from their opponent's backwards board...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
